{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01RRc1gy68LfK5nM5yujxEHJ","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"So `es-http` points to `elasticsearch-0/1/2` which use HTTPS. The precondition used `http://` which would fail (exit code 52 means empty reply from server). So `app-data` was NOT actually created successfully.\n\nWait, exit code 52 means \"empty reply from server\" - that's a curl error. The probe just ran the apply and was checking with `>/dev/null 2>&1; true` so it always succeeds. \n\nLooking at the precondition more carefully:\n- verify step uses `>/dev/null 2>&1; true` - always succeeds regardless of result\n- apply step also ends with `true`\n\nSo even though the HTTP call failed because HTTPS is required, the precondition still reported success by forcing true. This means `app-data` doesn't actually exist in the elasticsearch cluster.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1151,"cache_read_input_tokens":45123,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1151},"output_tokens":42,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"3a962eaa-a7c0-42f6-8f8c-e4f37a48e249","uuid":"5c78e0b3-fa9c-4c3e-889b-375e286a8445","request_id":"req_011CcN16Zu6crTjewqzqX8DZ"}
